content.description: 3 stars for being a nice warm up on mellow jugs low to the ground. Start far right sitting down and work your way left and up to the center of the wall.

Sit down start, left hand on 2-3 finger positive sloper, right hand on full hand sloper.  Move up to jug then follow the line of crimps which take you slightly right and up .  Massive undercling used on Boog's Big Dig is off.  Tops out either right and around the giant block going into poor quality honeycomb featured rock. I might have given it three stars if the top out wasnt so choss infested.  The movement and crimpy holds make for really good climbing.
content.protection: a Couple Crash pads, maybe a dab mat for the rock to your back as your make your way up and right.

content.description: SD Start left hand on crimp side pull, right hand on lower crimp, Move to Jugs and top out highest point on the wall or bail to the left.
Start Low and Far left, Work your way right on jugs and side pulls towards the center of the boulder .
Start low on jug and side pull, climb straight up on surf like side pulls to a large rail

One boulder sits on top of the other.  The upper boulder is a nice vertical section with a few climbs and is probably one of the best boulders to warm up on.  The few climbs here are full of good movement on really nice jugs that don't shred your hands.  The lower Boulder is a nicely overhung section of decent climbing low to the ground.  Topping out the lower boulder can be sketchy as you climb through a section of seemingly lower quality rock.
